comments: Garuba (HOU) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (HOU) briefly places his hand on Looney's (GSW) extended right arm and the contact at the start of the drive is marginal.
Thompson (GSW) deflects Porter Jr.'s (HOU) pass out of bounds. Possession is properly retained by Houston.
Porter Jr. (HOU) and Thompson (GSW) engage and disengage prior to the handoff and the contact is marginal.
Garuba (HOU) establishes himself in Thompson's (GSW) path and marginal contact occurs when Garuba turns to roll to the basket and engages with Thompson.
Looney (GSW) moves alongside Porter Jr.'s (HOU) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Garuba (HOU) makes contact with the ball and deflects it out of Thompson's (GSW) hand during the rebounding opportunity. Any arm contact after the dislodge is considered incidental.
Garuba (HOU) is the last player to come into contact with the ball prior to it falling out of bounds. Possession is properly awarded to Golden State.
Green (GSW) establishes himself in Porter Jr.'s (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs as Porter Jr. goes over the pick.
Garuba (HOU) places two hands to Looney's (GSW) side as he attempts to set the pick and the contact is marginal.
Smith Jr. (HOU) lightly brushes Wiggins' (GSW) left arm as Wiggins powers up to the basket. The contact on the play is marginal.
Wiggins (GSW) legally contests Porter Jr.'s (HOU) jump shot attempt.
Looney (GSW) brings two hands to Garuba's (HOU) back and extends out his arms, which dislodges Garuba from his legal rebounding position on the floor.
Following the whistled loose ball foul, the ensuing free throws are taken by Smith Jr. (HOU) but should have been attempted by Garuba.
Green (GSW) establishes himself in Garuba's (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players engage during the screen.
Gordon (HOU) legally contests Thompson's (GSW) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Poole (GSW) holds his forearm against Green's (HOU) side and the body contact during the drive is marginal.
Curry (GSW) lowers his hand down and makes contact with the ball and part of Green's (HOU) hand that is on the ball during his legal contest of Green's driving shot attempt.
Poole (GSW) and Garuba (HOU) come together in the air while pursuing the loose ball.
Smith Jr. (HOU) reaches in for the ball and initiates contact to Curry's (GSW) body that affects his SQBR at the start of his dribble.
Gordon (HOU) and Thompson (GSW) engage as Thompson sets the pick and the contact between the two players is marginal.
Gordon (HOU) steps towards Curry (GSW) as he changes direction and Curry is able to play on through the marginal body contact.
Curry (GSW) pins the ball against his side and brings his right hand underneath the ball during his dribble around the perimeter.
Curry's (GSW) left arm comes out and brushes Gordon (HOU) at the end of the drive.
Gordon (HOU) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
Martin Jr. (HOU) slips the pick and his left arm lightly brushes Poole's (GSW) arm.
Wiggins (GSW) initiates contact with Porter Jr.'s (HOU) arm after the release and the contact affects Porter Jr.'s follow through after the jump shot attempt.
Smith Jr. (HOU) and Green (GSW) get to ball height and deflect the rebound as it falls to the floor. The arm contact after the deflection is considered incidental.
Green (HOU) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Porter Jr. (HOU) does not inbound the ball within five seconds of having received it from the official.
Poole (GSW) and Green (HOU) engage as Green comes over the screen and the contact is marginal.
Thompson (GSW) legally contests Porter Jr.'s (HOU) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (HOU) drifts his left leg out slightly after the release of his jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Thompson (GSW).
